Step 7: Set Up Automated Deployment (Optional)
Using AWS CodePipeline:
Go to CodePipeline Console 
Create pipeline with:
Source: GitHub/CodeCommit
Build: CodeBuild (with Jekyll build commands)
Deploy: S3 deployment
CodeBuild buildspec.yml:
version: 0.2
phases:
  install:
    runtime-versions:
      ruby: 3.0
  pre_build:
    commands:
      - gem install bundler jekyll
      - bundle install
  build:
    commands:
      - jekyll build
  post_build:
    commands:
      - aws s3 sync _site/ s3://$BUCKET_NAME --delete
      - aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id $DISTRIBUTION_ID --paths "/*"

Important Notes:
MIME Type: Ensure .well-known/assetlinks.json serves with application/json content-type
Cache Invalidation: After updates, create CloudFront invalidation for /.well-known/*
HTTPS Required: Asset Links verification requires HTTPS
DNS Propagation: Allow 24-48 hours for full DNS propagation
Troubleshooting:
Blank page: Check CloudFront origin uses S3 website endpoint, not bucket endpoint
404 errors: Verify S3 static website hosting is enabled
SSL issues: Ensure certificate is in us-east-1 region
Asset Links not working: Verify JSON syntax and HTTPS accessibility
